An interesting article, from that it would appear that a great many people
failed to read the detail and took the &quot;Summary for Policymakers&quot; as being
the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth.

I think this paragraph sets the scene very nicely:-

&quot;Inevitably, many people have been bemused by this somewhat one-sided
debate, imagining that if so many experts are agreed, then there must be
something in it. But if we set the story of how this fear was promoted in
the context of other scares before it, the parallels which emerge might
leave any honest believer in global warming feeling uncomfortable.&quot;

Everyone knows that the Earth has gone through periods of hot and cold with
fluctuations within those periods, the only argument seems to be man's
influence since 1709 (the start of the Industrial Revolution). I'm not yet
convinced than man's activities are responsible. But having said that, it
seems to me that the less crap we pump into the environment in general the
better off we'll all be.
